\c 135
\cl Psalm 135
\s1 Confitemini Domino.
\cd God is to be praised for his wonderful works.
\p
\v 1 Alleluia.
\p Praise the Lord, for he is good: for his mercy endureth for ever.
\p
\v 2 Praise ye the God of gods: for his mercy endureth for ever.
\p
\v 3 Praise ye the Lord of lords: for his mercy endureth for ever.
\p
\v 4 Who alone doth great wonders: for his mercy endureth for ever.
\p
\v 5 *Who made the heavens in understanding: for his mercy endureth for ever.
\p
\v 6 Who established the earth above the waters: for his mercy endureth for ever.
\p
\v 7 Who made the great lights: for his mercy endureth for ever.
\p
\v 8 The sun to rule the day: for his mercy endureth for ever.
\p
\v 9 The moon and the stars to rule the night: for his mercy endureth for ever.
\p
\v 10 *Who smote Egypt with their first-born: for his mercy endureth for ever.
\p
\v 11 *Who brought Israel from among them: for his mercy endureth for ever.
\p
\v 12 With a mighty hand and with a stretched-out arm: for his mercy endureth for ever.
\p
\v 13 Who divided the Red Sea into parts: for his mercy endureth for ever.
\p
\v 14 And brought out Israel through the midst thereof: for his mercy endureth for ever.
\p
\v 15 *And overthrew Pharao and his host in the Red Sea: for his mercy endureth for ever.
\p
\v 16 Who led his people through the desert: for his mercy endureth for ever.
\p
\v 17 Who smote great kings: for his mercy endureth for ever.
\p
\v 18 *And slew strong kings: for his mercy endureth for ever.
\p
\v 19 Sehon, king of the Amorrhites: for his mercy endureth for ever.
\p
\v 20 *And Og, king of Basan: for his mercy endureth for ever.
\p
\v 21 *And he gave their land for an inheritance: for his mercy endureth for ever.
\p
\v 22 For an inheritance to his servant Israel: for his mercy endureth for ever.
\p
\v 23 For he was mindful of us in our affliction: for his mercy endureth for ever.
\p
\v 24 And he redeemed us from our enemies: for his mercy endureth for ever.
\p
\v 25 Who giveth food to all flesh: for his mercy endureth for ever.
\p
\v 26 Give glory to the God of heaven: for his mercy endureth for ever.
\p
\v 27 Give glory to the Lord of lords: for his mercy endureth for ever.
